1
00:00:38,487 --> 00:00:40,989
[ Dog Barking ]

2
00:00:40,989 --> 00:00:44,493
[ Man Whimpering ]

3
00:00:46,495 --> 00:00:51,500
???? [ Recording: Operatic
Contralto Aria ]

4
00:01:09,518 --> 00:01:13,021
[ Man Muttering ]

5
00:01:18,026 --> 00:01:20,529
HE'S DEAD.

6
00:01:21,530 --> 00:01:24,032
HE'S DEAD.

7
00:01:24,032 --> 00:01:27,035
[ Louder ]
I DON'T BELIEVE IT !
NO PULSE.

8
00:01:27,536 --> 00:01:31,039
THERE'S NO PULSE !
NO PULSE !  NO--

9
00:01:31,039 --> 00:01:34,543
YOU--
HE'S GOT NO PULSE.

10
00:01:42,050 --> 00:01:46,555
[ Moaning ]

11
00:01:49,057 --> 00:01:53,061
[ Panicked Murmuring ]

12
00:01:53,562 --> 00:01:55,564
[ Choking ]

13
00:03:42,170 --> 00:03:45,173
[ Man ]
A LITTLE AFTER MIDNIGHT,

14
00:03:45,173 --> 00:03:49,678
THE OLD CARETAKER WAS AWAKENED
BY A TERRIBLE SOUND;

15
00:03:49,678 --> 00:03:53,181
WHIMPERING, PITIFULLY.

16
00:03:53,181 --> 00:03:57,185
THE SOUND CAME AGAIN,
FAINTLY.

17
00:03:57,686 --> 00:04:02,190
ONLY THIS TIME
HE WAS SURE IT WAS HUMAN.

18
00:04:04,192 --> 00:04:06,194
THE GRAVEYARD WAS SILENT...

19
00:04:06,194 --> 00:04:09,698
EXCEPT FOR THE STEADY PADDING
OF HIS FEET...

20
00:04:10,198 --> 00:04:13,201
AS HE WENT
AROUND THE TOMBSTONES.

21
00:04:13,201 --> 00:04:17,205
"HELLO ?  IS SOMEONE THERE ?
SOMEONE ?"

22
00:04:17,205 --> 00:04:21,209
BUT THERE WAS NOTHING.
NO ONE.

23
00:04:21,710 --> 00:04:23,712
AS HE STOOD THERE,
SCRATCHING HIS HEAD,

24
00:04:24,212 --> 00:04:28,717
FEELING SOMETHING
OF A DAMN FOOL,

25
00:04:29,217 --> 00:04:30,719
HE HAPPENED TO LOOK DOWN.

26
00:04:31,219 --> 00:04:34,222
AND THERE AT HIS FEET,

27
00:04:34,723 --> 00:04:36,224
SOMEONE HAD BEEN BURIED...

28
00:04:36,725 --> 00:04:40,228
THAT VERY AFTERNOON.

29
00:04:40,228 --> 00:04:43,732
THE GRAVE HAD BEEN DISTURBED.

30
00:04:43,732 --> 00:04:48,737
THE SOIL WAS UPSET,
AND THE CROSS LAY ON ITS SIDE.

31
00:04:50,739 --> 00:04:53,241
"RESPECT," HE MUTTERED,

32
00:04:53,241 --> 00:04:56,244
SURE NOW THAT HE WAS THE
BUTT OF A PRACTICAL JOKE.

33
00:04:56,745 --> 00:05:00,749
SO HE SMOOTHED OUT THE SOIL...

34
00:05:00,749 --> 00:05:04,753
AND SET THE CROSS BACK UPRIGHT
AT THE HEAD OF THE GRAVE,

35
00:05:04,753 --> 00:05:08,256
AND THEN HE WENT BACK
TO HIS BED.

36
00:05:08,256 --> 00:05:10,759
BUT OUTSIDE,

37
00:05:10,759 --> 00:05:13,261
IN THE GRAVEYARD,

38
00:05:13,261 --> 00:05:15,263
IN THE WIND,

39
00:05:15,764 --> 00:05:19,768
THERE WAS STILL A FAINT WISP
OF SOUND,

40
00:05:19,768 --> 00:05:24,272
ALMOST LIKE A SONG:
[ Fingernails Scratching ]

41
00:05:24,272 --> 00:05:27,776
"ALIVE.  STILL ALIVE !"

42
00:05:29,277 --> 00:05:31,279
[ Faintly ]
AAAH !

43
00:05:31,279 --> 00:05:34,783
[ Whispering ]
"ALIVE."

44
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:45,794
[ Chuckles ]
GOD.

45
00:05:45,794 --> 00:05:48,797
[ Sighs ]
MARVELOUS STORY.

46
00:05:48,797 --> 00:05:50,799
MARVELOUS.

47
00:05:55,303 --> 00:05:57,806
I THINK THAT
WAS THE WORST SHOCKER
WE'VE HAD IN YEARS.

48
00:05:57,806 --> 00:06:00,809
DAMN NEAR SCARED THE PANTS
OFF ME, I'LL TELL YOU.
[ Chuckles ]

49
00:06:00,809 --> 00:06:03,311
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT YOU,

50
00:06:03,311 --> 00:06:05,814
BUT I COULD DO
WITH ANOTHER BRANDY.

51
00:06:05,814 --> 00:06:08,316
HEAR, HEAR.
MAYBE A GOOD CIGAR.

52
00:06:08,316 --> 00:06:10,318
I'VE GOT TO
GO TO BED.

53
00:06:10,318 --> 00:06:14,322
NO BRANDY ?
I HAVEN'T BEEN
SLEEPING WELL LATELY.

54
00:06:14,322 --> 00:06:16,825
BESIDES, IT'S LATE,
AND IT'S GETTING COLD.

55
00:06:17,325 --> 00:06:20,328
AND MILLY'LL BE WAITIN' UP TO--
POUR SOME HOT CHOCOLATE
DOWN ME.

56
00:06:20,328 --> 00:06:23,331
[ Laughs ]
COME ON.  I'LL
DRIVE YOU HOME, DOC.

57
00:06:23,331 --> 00:06:27,335
YOU KNOW, TEN YEARS FROM NOW,
80% OF THE YOUNG MEN
OF THIS COUNTRY...

58
00:06:27,335 --> 00:06:29,337
WILL BE WEARING TIES
ONLY TO WEDDINGS...

59
00:06:29,337 --> 00:06:31,339
AND--
AND TO FUNERALS
TOO, PERHAPS.

60
00:06:31,339 --> 00:06:33,341
I'D FEEL
AS IF I WAS NAKED.

61
00:06:33,341 --> 00:06:35,844
WELL, IT'S TIME
WE ALL WENT HOME.
COME ON, DOC.

62
00:06:35,844 --> 00:06:38,346
YOU LOOK TERRIBLE.
ARE YOU SLEEPING
ALL RIGHT ?

63
00:06:38,346 --> 00:06:41,349
DAMN IT TO HELL.
ARE YOU ?

64
00:06:41,349 --> 00:06:43,852
GENTLEMEN,
BEFORE YOU GO,

65
00:06:44,352 --> 00:06:46,855
I WOULD LIKE TO PROPOSE
A TOAST...

66
00:06:46,855 --> 00:06:51,359
TO US:
CHOWDER SOCIETY.

67
00:06:51,359 --> 00:06:53,361
CHOWDER SOCIETY.

68
00:06:53,361 --> 00:06:55,363
THE CHOWDER SOCIETY.
THE CHOWDER SOCIETY.

69
00:06:55,864 --> 00:06:58,366
[ Together ]
THE CHOWDER SOCIETY.

70
00:07:06,241 --> 00:07:09,244
[ Water Running ]

71
00:07:18,253 --> 00:07:21,256
WHO ARE YOU ?
[ Woman ]
SLEEPING.

72
00:07:21,256 --> 00:07:23,258
WHO ARE YOU ?

73
00:07:23,258 --> 00:07:25,260
WOKE ME.

74
00:07:27,262 --> 00:07:29,264
TELL ME !

75
00:07:32,767 --> 00:07:34,769
DAVID.

76
00:07:40,775 --> 00:07:44,779
- WHO ARE YOU ?
- YOU KNOW.

77
00:07:47,782 --> 00:07:49,784
I KNOW ?

78
00:07:52,287 --> 00:07:54,789
I AM YOU.

79
00:07:56,291 --> 00:07:58,293
NO.

80
00:08:00,295 --> 00:08:02,797
COLD.

81
00:08:16,811 --> 00:08:18,813
WHAT ARE YOU ?

82
00:08:22,317 --> 00:08:24,319
[ Screams ]

83
00:08:35,247 --> 00:08:37,249
[ Phone Ringing ]

84
00:08:41,753 --> 00:08:44,756
[ Ringing ]

85
00:08:51,146 --> 00:08:53,648
[ Engine Droning ]

86
00:08:53,648 --> 00:08:58,153
[ Man On Phone ]
DONNIE ?  COME HOME, DONNIE.

87
00:08:58,153 --> 00:09:01,656
THERE'S BEEN A TERRIBLE ACCIDENT
IN NEW YORK.

88
00:09:03,658 --> 00:09:07,162
YOUR BROTHER IS...
DEAD, SON.

89
00:09:07,162 --> 00:09:10,165
COME HOME RIGHT AWAY.

90
00:09:16,171 --> 00:09:20,175
[ Man On P.A. ]
NOW ARRIVING AT GATE THREE
FROM NEW YORK,

91
00:09:20,175 --> 00:09:24,179
HARTFORD AND SPRINGFIELD.

92
00:09:24,179 --> 00:09:27,182
GATE THREE FROM NEW YORK,

93
00:09:27,182 --> 00:09:29,684
HARTFORD AND SPRINGFIELD.
BE CAREFUL.

94
00:09:30,685 --> 00:09:34,189
[ Passengers Chattering ]

95
00:09:34,689 --> 00:09:38,193
[ P.A. ]
BUS FOR MONTREAL--
HELLO, DAD.

96
00:09:38,193 --> 00:09:41,696
WELL--  IS THIS
ALL YOU HAVE ?

97
00:09:42,197 --> 00:09:44,199
I'M FINE.

98
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:48,703
- L-LOOK AT YOU.
- I'M OKAY, DAD.

99
00:09:48,703 --> 00:09:52,707
[ P.A. ]
MONTPELIER,
YOUR GATE IS FOUR.

100
00:09:52,707 --> 00:09:55,210
[ Radio Announcer ]
BREAK OUT THE SNOWMOBILES,
BOYS AND GIRLS.

101
00:09:55,710 --> 00:09:59,214
TWO INCHES OF THAT LOVELY
WHITE STUFF ALREADY
ON THE GROUND...

102
00:09:59,214 --> 00:10:01,616
AND A MASSIVE COLD FRONT
HEADING OUR WAY.

103
00:10:01,616 --> 00:10:03,585
NO QUESTION ABOUT IT.

104
00:10:18,099 --> 00:10:20,602
TALKIN' ABOUT IT
MIGHT HELP.

105
00:10:22,604 --> 00:10:24,606
[ Exhales ]
RIGHT.

106
00:10:27,609 --> 00:10:30,612
[ Sighs ]
HOW'S THE WRITING
COMING ?

107
00:10:30,612 --> 00:10:33,114
I'VE HAD OTHER THINGS
ON MY MIND.

108
00:10:33,114 --> 00:10:36,618
TEACHING ?
DIDN'T FINISH OUT
THE TERM.

109
00:10:38,119 --> 00:10:39,621
OH, DON.

110
00:10:41,122 --> 00:10:44,125
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK
HAPPENED TO HIM, DAD ?

111
00:10:45,627 --> 00:10:47,128
THIS WAS AN ACCIDENT.

112
00:10:47,629 --> 00:10:50,131
OH, IS THAT WHAT YOU
TOLD EVERYBODY ?

113
00:10:50,131 --> 00:10:53,635
WHAT, THAT HE FELL ?
THAT'S WHAT THEY SAID.

114
00:10:54,135 --> 00:10:55,637
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN !

115
00:10:56,137 --> 00:10:59,641
I KNOW SOMETHING HAPPENED
TO HIM IN NEW YORK.
YOU'RE SHOUTIN'.

116
00:10:59,641 --> 00:11:03,144
JESUS CHRIST, DAD !
I'M TELLING YOU SOMETHING
HAPPENED TO HIM !

117
00:11:03,144 --> 00:11:05,647
HE MAY HAVE BEEN MURDERED !
STOP IT !

118
00:11:11,152 --> 00:11:14,656
[ Breathing Heavily ]

119
00:11:17,158 --> 00:11:20,161
I KNEW THE GIRL
HE WAS GONNA MARRY.

120
00:11:22,664 --> 00:11:27,168
I SLEPT WITH HER, DAD.
DO YOU HEAR ME ?

121
00:11:27,168 --> 00:11:29,170
- I SLEPT WITH HER.
-[ Dishes Crash ]

122
00:11:31,673 --> 00:11:35,677
YOU COME HERE LOOKING LIKE
GOD KNOWS WHAT,

123
00:11:35,677 --> 00:11:38,179
YOUR BROTHER
NOT EVEN IN HIS GRAVE YET--

124
00:11:38,179 --> 00:11:40,181
DAD--

125
00:11:40,181 --> 00:11:45,186
AND YOU START CARRYING ON
ABOUT HAVING SEX
WITH HIS FIANCEE.

126
00:11:45,186 --> 00:11:50,692
- DAD !
- ISN'T IT ABOUT TIME
YOU STRAIGHTENED OUT ?

127
00:11:52,694 --> 00:11:54,696
SOMEHOW.

128
00:11:56,698 --> 00:11:58,666
DAD.

129
00:12:02,420 --> 00:12:06,925
[ Minister ]
I WILL FEAR NO EVIL,
FOR THOU ART WITH ME.

130
00:12:06,925 --> 00:12:09,928
THY ROD AND THY STAFF--

131
00:12:10,428 --> 00:12:12,430
THOU PREPAREST A TABLE--
DAVID.

132
00:12:12,430 --> 00:12:16,935
SURELY GOODNESS
AND MERCY SHALL FOLLOW ME
ALL THE DAYS OF MY LIFE.

133
00:12:25,443 --> 00:12:30,448
[ Moaning ]

134
00:12:34,452 --> 00:12:37,956
[ Muttering Incoherently ]

135
00:12:38,456 --> 00:12:39,958
DAVID.  DAVID.

136
00:12:40,458 --> 00:12:42,460
[ Cries Out ]

137
00:12:47,465 --> 00:12:48,967
DON.

138
00:12:49,467 --> 00:12:54,472
OH !  I-- I DIDN'T KNOW
WHERE I WAS FOR A MOMENT.

139
00:12:55,473 --> 00:12:58,476
YOU WERE HAVIN'
A BAD DREAM.

140
00:12:58,476 --> 00:13:00,478
LORD, WAS I EVER.
[ Chuckles ]

141
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:05,984
THINK I'LL TURN IN.

142
00:13:05,984 --> 00:13:07,986
GOOD NIGHT.
NIGHT.

143
00:13:10,989 --> 00:13:14,492
WELL, YOU'RE ALL I HAVE
LEFT NOW, YOU KNOW.

144
00:13:17,996 --> 00:13:20,999
[ Inhales ]
UH, MAYBE--

145
00:13:20,999 --> 00:13:24,002
UH, MAYBE
IF THE WEATHER LETS UP,

146
00:13:24,002 --> 00:13:28,506
YOU AND I CAN GO FISHIN'
ONE DAY.

147
00:13:28,506 --> 00:13:30,508
I-I'D LIKE THAT.

148
00:13:30,508 --> 00:13:33,011
ME TOO.

149
00:13:35,513 --> 00:13:41,019
WELL, STAY AROUND A FEW DAYS
AND HELP YOUR OLD MAN OUT
WITH A FEW THINGS.

150
00:13:41,019 --> 00:13:43,021
WHATEVER YOU SAY.
SURE.

151
00:13:52,030 --> 00:13:55,033
DON'T FORGET TO LOCK UP,
WILL YOU, KIDDO ?

152
00:13:58,887 --> 00:14:01,372
[ Woman Chuckling ]

153
00:14:02,874 --> 00:14:05,376
[ Moaning ]

154
00:14:05,376 --> 00:14:09,380
[ Woman Moaning ]

155
00:14:09,380 --> 00:14:11,883
[ Sobs ]

156
00:14:11,883 --> 00:14:14,385
[ Woman Laughing ]

157
00:14:17,388 --> 00:14:21,392
- [ Crying ]
-[ Woman ]
WAKE UP.  WAKE UP !

158
00:14:21,392 --> 00:14:25,396
[ Yelling ]
NOOOO !
RICKY, FOR GOD'S SAKE !

159
00:14:25,396 --> 00:14:28,399
STELLA.

160
00:14:28,399 --> 00:14:30,902
MY GOD.

161
00:14:31,402 --> 00:14:33,905
WOW.
HERE.

162
00:14:45,416 --> 00:14:49,420
[ Sighs ]
YOU POOR DARLING.

163
00:14:52,924 --> 00:14:55,927
BETTER ?
YEAH.

164
00:14:59,430 --> 00:15:01,432
YOU WANNA TELL ME
ABOUT IT ?

165
00:15:01,432 --> 00:15:03,434
NO, NO, NO.

166
00:15:04,936 --> 00:15:06,938
OH.

167
00:15:06,938 --> 00:15:09,941
THOSE GRUESOME STORIES
YOU TELL EACH OTHER.

168
00:15:09,941 --> 00:15:12,443
IT'S A WONDER
YOU CAN SLEEP AT ALL.

169
00:15:13,945 --> 00:15:18,950
WHAT ARE YOU OLD FOOLS
UP TO ?
BLACK MAGIC.

170
00:15:21,953 --> 00:15:23,955
YOU'RE NUTS.

171
00:15:31,462 --> 00:15:34,966
[ Moaning ]

172
00:15:46,978 --> 00:15:50,982
[ Eerie Shrieks, Muffled ]

173
00:16:01,492 --> 00:16:05,496
[ Muffled Moaning ]

174
00:16:05,496 --> 00:16:08,499
[ Crying Out ]

175
00:16:10,001 --> 00:16:12,003
DAD ?

176
00:16:12,003 --> 00:16:14,005
[ Crying Out ]

177
00:16:17,008 --> 00:16:21,512
[ Crying Out ]
DAD ?

178
00:16:21,512 --> 00:16:23,514
DAD, YOU OKAY ?

179
00:16:25,016 --> 00:16:28,019
FINE.  FINE.
[ Exhales ]

180
00:16:28,519 --> 00:16:33,024
YOU SURE ?
IT WAS--
IT WAS JUST A DREAM.

181
00:16:33,024 --> 00:16:35,026
ARE YOU SURE ?
[ Rattling Lock ]

182
00:16:41,032 --> 00:16:44,535
[ Woman Weeping ]

183
00:17:25,359 --> 00:17:27,862
MORNING, MR. MAYOR.

184
00:17:29,864 --> 00:17:31,866
IS EVERYTHING OKAY ?

185
00:17:33,868 --> 00:17:37,371
THE WIFE AND I...
WE'RE SORRY ABOUT YOUR LOSS.
TERRIBLE THING.

186
00:17:55,389 --> 00:17:57,892
DAVID !

187
00:18:00,394 --> 00:18:03,397
DAVID !

188
00:18:03,397 --> 00:18:05,900
DAVID !

189
00:18:07,401 --> 00:18:09,403
DAVID !

190
00:18:15,910 --> 00:18:17,912
DAVID !

191
00:18:48,442 --> 00:18:51,445
WHAT THE HELL IS HE--

192
00:18:54,448 --> 00:18:57,451
[ Woman ]
NED ?

193
00:18:57,451 --> 00:18:59,453
NED.

194
00:19:04,425 --> 00:19:06,878
- NED !
- [ Screams ]

195
00:19:27,899 --> 00:19:29,901
HOLY SHIT.

196
00:19:32,403 --> 00:19:37,408
[ Snickering ]

197
00:19:42,496 --> 00:19:44,498
[ Phones Ringing ]
[ Man ]
RICK, THAT'S PATHETIC !

198
00:19:44,498 --> 00:19:47,501
THANK GOD YOU'RE BACK !
EVERYONE'S BEEN CALLING !
A NINNY !

199
00:19:47,501 --> 00:19:52,006
AND SO ARE YOU,
IF YOU KEEP BELIEVING
SUCH TWADDLE !

200
00:19:52,006 --> 00:19:54,508
HE SAW HIM !
EDWARD WAS DOING SOMETHING
ON THAT BRIDGE.

201
00:19:54,508 --> 00:19:56,510
I CAN'T IMAGINE WHAT,
BUT SOMETHING !

202
00:19:56,510 --> 00:19:58,512
HE WAS WALKING--
I HAVE ANOTHER IDEA.

203
00:19:58,512 --> 00:20:03,017
[ Phones Continue Ringing ]
WE'VE GOT TO HELP THE BOY.

204
00:20:03,517 --> 00:20:06,520
YOU TALK AS IF HE WAS
12 YEARS OLD.

205
00:20:07,021 --> 00:20:08,522
I'M SURE EDWARD LEFT HIM
WELL PROVIDED FOR.

206
00:20:09,023 --> 00:20:13,527
- WHY DON'T YOU TELL HIM
HOW GRATEFUL HE SHOULD BE ?
- TAKE IT EASY, NOW.

207
00:20:13,527 --> 00:20:16,530
TO KNOW A MAN OVER 50 YEARS.

208
00:20:16,530 --> 00:20:19,033
YOU-- YOU'D THINK YOU KNEW
WHAT HE WAS CAPABLE OF !

209
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:23,037
YOU'RE NOT DOING YOUR
BLOOD PRESSURE ANY GOOD.

210
00:20:23,537 --> 00:20:26,040
MYBLOOD ?

211
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,542
MR. JAMES, IT'S JOEL BRENNER
OVER AT THEURBANITE.

212
00:20:29,043 --> 00:20:32,546
WANTS TO KNOW IF YOU'LL WRITE
SOMETHING ABOUT THE MAYOR
FOR THE PAPER.

213
00:20:32,546 --> 00:20:35,549
- RICKY, YOU TAKE CARE OF IT.
- WHAT SHALL I SAY ?

214
00:20:36,050 --> 00:20:38,552
MY GOD.  HE WENT
OFF THE BRIDGE !

215
00:20:39,053 --> 00:20:42,056
SAY WHATEVER YOU DAMN PLEASE.

216
00:20:42,056 --> 00:20:45,059
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

217
00:20:45,059 --> 00:20:48,562
- COME ON, COME ON.
YOU BETTER--
- I CAN'T BELIEVE IT !

218
00:20:48,562 --> 00:20:50,564
COME ON, YOU BETTER
GO HOME NOW.

219
00:20:53,567 --> 00:20:55,569
YOU-- YOU--
I'LL CALL YOU LATER.

220
00:20:55,569 --> 00:20:59,573
YOU KNEW HIM AS WELL AS I DID,
RICKY.  HE COULDN'T.

221
00:20:59,573 --> 00:21:01,575
IDON'TBELIEVE IT !

222
00:21:04,578 --> 00:21:07,081
NOT NOW, RICKY.

223
00:21:09,083 --> 00:21:11,519
YES.  NOW.

224
00:22:10,695 --> 00:22:12,697
MY GOD, SEARS.

225
00:22:13,197 --> 00:22:16,701
SOMETHING'S HAPPENING.
I-- I CAN TELL.

226
00:22:16,701 --> 00:22:19,704
SOMETHING TERRIBLE.
YOU CAN BE VERY PERSISTENT.

227
00:22:20,204 --> 00:22:23,207
PERSISTENT
WITHOUT BEING A BULLY.

228
00:22:23,207 --> 00:22:25,209
THAT'S A VERY NICE QUALITY,
RICKY.

229
00:22:25,209 --> 00:22:29,714
- DON'T TRY TO BAMBOOZLE ME.
- IT'S A FEW BAD DREAMS !

230
00:22:29,714 --> 00:22:34,719
AND A MONTHLY SPOOK STORY.
COME ON, NOW.
LET'S GET TO WORK.

231
00:22:34,719 --> 00:22:36,721
YOU'RE DISSEMBLING.
IT'S BENEATH YOU.

232
00:22:37,221 --> 00:22:40,224
ALL RIGHT.

233
00:22:40,224 --> 00:22:42,226
WHAT WOULD YOU ADVISE ?

234
00:22:45,229 --> 00:22:49,734
I DON'T KNOW.  BUT WE'VE
GOTTA DO SOMETHING.

235
00:23:19,764 --> 00:23:21,766
[ Woman Chuckles ]

236
00:23:33,778 --> 00:23:37,281
[ Laughter Continues ]

237
00:24:19,607 --> 00:24:23,110
HELLO.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE ?

238
00:24:23,110 --> 00:24:25,112
ANSWER ME.
I WON'T HURT YOU.

239
00:24:25,112 --> 00:24:27,114
[ Man ]
ANSWER THE MAN, FENNY.

240
00:24:27,615 --> 00:24:29,617
HELLO, MR. HAWTHORNE.

241
00:24:31,619 --> 00:24:34,622
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE ?
WHAT DO YOU WANT ?

242
00:24:35,122 --> 00:24:38,125
WE WANT TO PLAY.
ISN'T THAT SO,
LITTLE BROTHER ?

243
00:24:38,125 --> 00:24:40,127
[ Giggles ]

244
00:24:40,628 --> 00:24:43,130
YOU CAN'T STAY HERE.
YOU'RE BREAKING THE LAW.

245
00:24:43,130 --> 00:24:46,634
- IS THAT SO ?
- YOU'RE TRESPASSING HERE,
ILLEGALLY !

246
00:24:47,134 --> 00:24:50,137
NO.  NO, WE'RE NOT.

247
00:24:54,141 --> 00:24:56,143
- WE KNOW THE OWNER.
- THERE IS NO OWNER.

248
00:24:56,644 --> 00:25:00,147
SURE, THERE IS !
WE'VE SPOKEN TO HER.

249
00:25:00,147 --> 00:25:03,651
- WHO ?
- OUR FRIEND.

250
00:25:04,151 --> 00:25:06,153
OUR NEW FRIEND.

251
00:25:07,154 --> 00:25:09,657
NO ONE LIVES HERE.
SOMEONE LIVED HERE.

252
00:25:11,158 --> 00:25:13,160
SOMEONE FANTASTIC.

253
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:16,163
WHAT ?

254
00:25:16,664 --> 00:25:19,166
YOU'VE LIVED IN THIS TOWN
ALL YOUR LIFE,
AND YOU DON'T KNOW ?

255
00:25:19,166 --> 00:25:21,669
WHAT ?

256
00:25:22,670 --> 00:25:24,672
HE KNOWS,
DOESN'T HE, FENNY ?

257
00:25:35,182 --> 00:25:37,184
[ Growls ]
MAYBE HE'D LIKE TO PLAY
WITH US, FENNY.

258
00:25:37,184 --> 00:25:40,187
WHAT ?
MAYBE IT'S TIME
HE JOINED OUR LITTLE GAME.

259
00:25:40,187 --> 00:25:42,690
YEAH.  YOU'RE GONNA BE
SEEING SOME UNUSUAL...

260
00:25:42,690 --> 00:25:45,693
AND INTERESTING THINGS
BEFORE WE'RE THROUGH,
RICKY !

261
00:25:45,693 --> 00:25:48,195
NO.
AND YOU MIGHT SAY...

262
00:25:48,195 --> 00:25:51,699
YOU'RE GONNA BE HAVING
THE TIME OF YOUR LIFE.

263
00:25:51,699 --> 00:25:54,201
YOU KNOW, RICKY,

264
00:25:54,201 --> 00:25:57,204
YOU'RE NOT GONNA KNOW
IF YOU'RE REAPING OR SOWING.

265
00:25:57,204 --> 00:26:00,207
YOU WON'T KNOW UP
FROM DOWN.  AND, RICKY,

266
00:26:00,207 --> 00:26:03,210
WE'RE GOING TO TEAR THE SOUL
OF THIS PATHETIC TOWN...

267
00:26:03,711 --> 00:26:06,714
AND CRUSH ITS BARE BONES
BETWEEN OUR TEETH !

268
00:26:11,218 --> 00:26:14,221
[ Fenny Giggles ]
[ Man ]  FENNY DID GOOD,
DIDN'T HE, LADY ?

269
00:26:14,221 --> 00:26:17,224
[ Woman ]
EXCELLENT.
YOU LIKED THAT, DIDN'T YOU ?

270
00:26:17,224 --> 00:26:21,228
[ Woman ]
I LOVED IT.  NOW I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT WE'RE GOING TO DO NEXT.

271
00:26:35,242 --> 00:26:37,244
THAT'S HIM !

272
00:26:40,748 --> 00:26:42,249
GREGORY BATE.

273
00:26:42,750 --> 00:26:45,753
ARE YOU SURE,
MR. HAWTHORNE ?

274
00:26:45,753 --> 00:26:47,755
POSITIVE.

275
00:26:48,222 --> 00:26:50,724
[ Bell Tolling ]

276
00:27:01,735 --> 00:27:03,737
THE EVIDENCE,
TAKEN AS A WHOLE,

277
00:27:04,238 --> 00:27:07,741
LEADS ME TO ONLY ONE
POSSIBLE CONCLUSION.

278
00:27:07,741 --> 00:27:12,746
THAT EDWARD CHARLES WANDERLEY,
HIS MIND IN A STATE
OF CONFUSION,

279
00:27:13,247 --> 00:27:15,749
TOOK HIS OWN LIFE.
[ Man ]
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS !

280
00:27:15,749 --> 00:27:19,253
GET THEM OUT OF THAT HOUSE
TODAY.  DO YOU HEAR ME ?

281
00:27:19,253 --> 00:27:21,255
I'M SURE EVERYBODY
HAS BY NOW.

282
00:27:21,755 --> 00:27:24,758
DON'T SMART-ASS ME.
JUST GET 'EM OUTTA THERE.

283
00:27:25,259 --> 00:27:28,262
SEARS JAMES,
I DON'T SUPPOSE
THERE'S ANY MAN ALIVE...

284
00:27:28,262 --> 00:27:30,264
WHO EVER GOT IN
THE LAST WORD WITH YOU.

285
00:27:30,264 --> 00:27:32,266
I SHOULD HOPE
TO HELL NOT !

286
00:27:34,768 --> 00:27:38,272
MR. HAWTHORNE.
MEET ME AT THE VILLAGE
PUMP IN HALF AN HOUR.

287
00:27:44,778 --> 00:27:48,282
[ Officer On Police Radio ]
IT'S JUST LIKE MR. HAWTHORNE
SAID, WALT.  BATE IS CRAZY.

288
00:27:48,782 --> 00:27:51,285
"EXTREMELY UNSTABLE,"
IT SAYS HERE.

289
00:27:51,785 --> 00:27:55,789
HE AND THE BOY ESCAPED
FROM A STATE MENTAL HOSPITAL
ABOUT A MONTH AGO.

290
00:27:58,792 --> 00:28:02,796
AND, WALT...
HE WAS A MEMBER OF SOME KIND
OF OCCULT ORDER...

291
00:28:02,796 --> 00:28:04,798
BACK IN CALIFORNIA.

292
00:28:04,798 --> 00:28:07,801
[ Walt ]
GEEZ, WHAT A PAIR !

293
00:28:07,801 --> 00:28:10,304
MM, WALT !
WHAT ABOUT THIS OCCULT
BUSINESS ?

294
00:28:10,304 --> 00:28:12,806
YOU THINK THERE'S
ANYTHING TO IT ?

295
00:28:13,307 --> 00:28:15,309
I AIN'T NO FREUD.

296
00:28:21,815 --> 00:28:26,320
DAMN FUNNY WORLD.
GETTIN' TO BE
A DAMN FUNNY WORLD.

297
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:29,823
[ Patrons Chattering ]

298
00:28:29,823 --> 00:28:32,326
STRANGEST THINGS
POP INTO MY HEAD.

299
00:28:32,326 --> 00:28:35,829
I WAS JUST THINKING
THAT SIDEWALKS
HAVE CHANGED THE WORLD.

300
00:28:35,829 --> 00:28:39,333
-ONE OF MY EARLIEST
RECOLLECTIONS IS--
- MR. HAWTHORNE ?

301
00:28:39,833 --> 00:28:43,337
CALL ME RICKY.  EVERYBODY DOES.
GETTING BACK TO SIDEWALKS,

302
00:28:43,337 --> 00:28:45,839
YOUR FATHER AND I
USED TO--
MR. HAWTHORNE.

303
00:28:50,844 --> 00:28:54,348
YOU DIDN'T ASK ME HERE
TO TALK ABOUT SIDEWALKS,
DID YOU ?

304
00:28:55,849 --> 00:28:59,853
[ Sighs ]
NO.  NO.

305
00:29:02,356 --> 00:29:06,860
[ Sighs ]
SEARS WOULD BRAIN ME
FOR SAYING THIS,

306
00:29:07,361 --> 00:29:08,862
BUT I THINK
WE'RE IN DANGER.

307
00:29:09,363 --> 00:29:13,867
ALL OF US: MILBURN,
THE CHOWDER SOCIETY.

308
00:29:17,871 --> 00:29:20,374
ESPECIALLY
THE CHOWDER SOCIETY.

309
00:29:21,875 --> 00:29:24,378
WHO IS THIS ?

310
00:29:54,908 --> 00:29:57,911
I'M NEVER GONNA FIND NOTHIN'.

311
00:29:57,911 --> 00:30:00,914
ONLY A PAIR OF LOONIES.

312
00:30:03,417 --> 00:30:05,419
COCKAMAMIE !

313
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:09,423
SOMEONE'S IDEA OF A JOKE.

314
00:30:20,934 --> 00:30:23,937
[ Screeching ]

315
00:30:36,650 --> 00:30:41,154
[ Noise Of
Elevator Rising ]

316
00:30:56,169 --> 00:31:00,173
[ Noise Continues ]

317
00:31:02,175 --> 00:31:04,177
[ Noise Stops ]

318
00:31:29,202 --> 00:31:31,204
[ Elevator Noises Resume ]

319
00:32:03,236 --> 00:32:05,238
THE LORD IS MY SHEPHERD,

320
00:32:05,238 --> 00:32:09,242
I SHALL NOT WANT.

321
00:32:09,242 --> 00:32:12,746
HE MAKETH ME TO LIE DOWN
IN GREEN PASTURES.

322
00:32:12,746 --> 00:32:15,248
HE RESTORETH--
HOW DID YOU
GET IN HERE ?

323
00:32:19,753 --> 00:32:23,256
SUCH A TRAGEDY.

324
00:32:23,256 --> 00:32:25,759
I'M SO VERY SORRY.

325
00:32:34,267 --> 00:32:37,771
WHAT KIND OF WELCOME
IS THAT, DON ?

326
00:32:37,771 --> 00:32:40,774
SOMEONE'S DIED HERE.

327
00:32:41,274 --> 00:32:43,276
WHAT DO YOU WANT ?

328
00:32:46,279 --> 00:32:48,281
HOW DO YOU KNOW MY NAME ?

329
00:32:50,283 --> 00:32:52,285
TO LOOK.

330
00:32:56,289 --> 00:32:58,291
TO TOUCH.
???? [ Plays Organ Note ]

331
00:32:59,292 --> 00:33:01,795
WHO ARE YOU ?

332
00:33:01,795 --> 00:33:04,798
MY NAME IS GREGORY BATE,

333
00:33:04,798 --> 00:33:07,801
ALTHOUGH I'VE BEEN KNOWN
BY OTHER NAMES IN OTHER PLACES.

334
00:33:07,801 --> 00:33:09,803
GET OUT !

335
00:33:11,805 --> 00:33:14,307
ARE YOU AFRAID, DON ?

336
00:33:14,307 --> 00:33:19,312
WILL YOU BE AFRAID WHEN
YOU WALK THROUGH THE VALLEY
OF THE SHADOW OF DEATH ?

337
00:33:20,814 --> 00:33:22,816
YOU'RE CRAZY.

338
00:33:22,816 --> 00:33:26,820
GREAT TREATS ARE IN STORE
FOR YOU AND YOUR OLD FRIENDS.

339
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:31,324
IMAGINE.
JUST IMAGINE.

340
00:33:31,324 --> 00:33:34,327
- GET THE HELL OUT !
- WE'RE FULL OF SURPRISES,
AREN'T WE, FENNY ?

341
00:33:34,828 --> 00:33:38,331
- [ Snarls ]
- [ Yells ]
- [ Gregory ]  GOOD BOY.

342
00:33:38,331 --> 00:33:42,836
WE DO HAVE SOMETHING SPECIAL
FOR DON, DON'T WE ?

343
00:33:51,344 --> 00:33:54,347
IT'S A LITTLE PRESENT
FROM OUR BENEFACTOR.

344
00:34:00,854 --> 00:34:02,856
WHERE DID YOU GET THAT ?

345
00:34:10,864 --> 00:34:15,869
[ Sears ]
EVERY WINTER.
ICE.  THE POWER LINES.

346
00:34:21,875 --> 00:34:23,877
YOU SHOULD
SEE YOURSELVES.

347
00:34:23,877 --> 00:34:27,881
YOU LOOK LIKE
THREE OWLS.
LEAVE THE CANDLES, MILLY.

348
00:34:29,883 --> 00:34:33,887
YOU'RE GIVING
EACH OTHER THE WILLIES
WITH THESE MEETINGS.

349
00:34:43,396 --> 00:34:45,398
- HE'S FOUND A PICTURE OF HER.
-[ Sears ]
WHO ?

350
00:34:45,398 --> 00:34:47,901
- DON.
- BUT THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.
I THOUGHT WE--

351
00:34:47,901 --> 00:34:49,903
I'M AFRAID EDWARD KEPT ONE.

352
00:34:49,903 --> 00:34:52,906
- WHAT HAVE YOU TOLD HIM ?
- NOTHING.

353
00:34:53,406 --> 00:34:54,908
I WANTED TO.
I LIKE THE BOY.

354
00:34:55,408 --> 00:34:59,412
- THE CIRCLE
HAS HELD THIS LONG.
- MAYBE HE CAN HELP US.

355
00:34:59,412 --> 00:35:04,918
- CHANGE IS CHANGE
FOR THE WORSE !
- SPOKEN LIKE A TRUE LAWYER.

356
00:35:04,918 --> 00:35:06,920
HUH !

357
00:35:07,921 --> 00:35:11,424
WE CAN FEEL THINGS
WATCHING US
AND FOLLOWING US,

358
00:35:11,424 --> 00:35:14,928
AND WE DISMISS THEM
AS FANTASIES.

359
00:35:16,429 --> 00:35:19,933
WE HAVE NIGHTMARES
AND TRY TO FORGET THEM.

360
00:35:19,933 --> 00:35:23,436
NOW THAT EDWARD'S GONE,

361
00:35:23,436 --> 00:35:26,439
I FEAR--
I VERY MUCH FEAR...

362
00:35:26,439 --> 00:35:28,942
THAT MORE OF US
ARE GOING TO DIE.

363
00:35:28,942 --> 00:35:30,944
[ Don ]
I THINK HE'S RIGHT.

364
00:35:31,444 --> 00:35:35,448
- I TOLD HIM
YOU WEREN'T TO BE DISTURBED.
- THAT'LL BE ALL, MILLY.

365
00:35:37,450 --> 00:35:40,453
- MILLY.
- WELL, THEN, I'LL JUST
LEAVE YOU GENTLEMEN...

366
00:35:40,453 --> 00:35:42,455
TO YOUR PRIVATE BUSINESS.

367
00:35:43,957 --> 00:35:49,129
WELL, YOUNG MAN,
DO YOU HAVE SOMETHING
TO SAY TO US ?

368
00:35:50,130 --> 00:35:52,132
I WANT TO BUY MY WAY
INTO THE CHOWDER SOCIETY.

369
00:35:52,132 --> 00:35:54,634
BUY ?
WHAT DID YOU SAY ?

370
00:35:56,136 --> 00:35:58,138
WITH A STORY.
ISN'T THAT THE PRICE
OF ADMISSION ?

371
00:36:02,142 --> 00:36:03,643
I'M SORRY, MR. HAWTHORNE.

372
00:36:04,144 --> 00:36:06,146
RICKY.

373
00:36:06,646 --> 00:36:11,151
BUT IT'S WORSE THAN YOU KNOW.
AT LEAST TWO PEOPLE
HAVE ALREADY DIED.

374
00:36:11,651 --> 00:36:14,654
MY BROTHER WAS THE FIRST.
[ Inhales ]

375
00:36:14,654 --> 00:36:18,158
I THINK THIS IS
A GHOST STORY.

376
00:36:23,163 --> 00:36:27,667
I HAD LANDED A...
YEAR'S TEACHING JOB...

377
00:36:27,667 --> 00:36:32,172
AT A SMALL LIBERAL ARTS
COLLEGE JUST NORTH
OF ORLANDO, FLORIDA.

378
00:36:32,172 --> 00:36:35,675
PRETTY UNROMANTIC STUFF,
REALLY.  JUST A COUPLE
OF SECTIONS...

379
00:36:35,675 --> 00:36:40,680
OF AN UNDERGRADUATE COURSE
IN AMERICAN LITERATURE.
[ Man ]  WAIT UP !

380
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:45,685
I WAS SEEING-- I WAS SORT OF
SEEING THIS OTHER INSTRUCTOR,

381
00:36:45,685 --> 00:36:47,687
A GIRL NAMED HELEN KAYON.
[ Bell Ringing ]

382
00:36:50,190 --> 00:36:53,193
MR. WANDERLEY.

383
00:36:57,197 --> 00:37:00,700
- WHO WAS THAT ?
-THE DEAN'S NEW SECRETARY.
JUST STARTED TODAY.

384
00:37:00,700 --> 00:37:04,704
- HOW'D SHE KNOW WHO I WAS ?
- IT MUST BE THOSE BLUE EYES
OF YOURS.

385
00:37:05,205 --> 00:37:07,207
[ Laughs ]
RIGHT.

386
00:37:07,207 --> 00:37:09,709
- CALL ME TONIGHT.
- ALL RIGHT.

387
00:37:12,712 --> 00:37:16,716
"AND THE FIRST THING
SHE DOES IS SEDUCE HIM.

388
00:37:16,716 --> 00:37:19,219
"THE FIRST THING HE DOES
IS TO BE SEDUCED.

389
00:37:19,219 --> 00:37:22,222
"AND THE SECOND THING
THEY DO...

390
00:37:22,222 --> 00:37:25,225
"IS HUG THEIR SIN
IN SECRET...

391
00:37:25,225 --> 00:37:27,727
"AND GLOAT OVER IT.

392
00:37:27,727 --> 00:37:30,730
AND TRY TO UNDERSTAND."

393
00:37:30,730 --> 00:37:33,233
WHICH IS THE MYTH
OF NEW ENGLAND.

394
00:37:35,235 --> 00:37:36,736
BETWEEN NOW
AND THE NEXT TIME WE MEET,

395
00:37:37,237 --> 00:37:39,739
I'D LIKE YOU TO THINK ABOUT
WHAT D.H. LAWRENCE MEANT
WHEN HE WROTE THAT.

396
00:37:43,243 --> 00:37:45,245
DO YOU HAVE A QUESTION,
MR. SOLT ?

397
00:37:45,245 --> 00:37:46,746
YEAH, THE PART
ABOUT SEDUCTION.

398
00:37:47,247 --> 00:37:49,716
- YES ?
- COULD YOU BE
A LITTLE MORE SPECIFIC ?

399
00:37:49,716 --> 00:37:53,720
[ Students Laugh ]
NEXT TIME.

400
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:56,222
[ Typewriter Tapping ]

401
00:38:03,229 --> 00:38:05,732
SO YOU'RE WORKIN' LATE,
HUH ?
MR. WANDERLEY.

402
00:38:08,234 --> 00:38:12,238
NO, THAT'S NOT REALLY FAIR,
IS IT ?  YOU KNOW MY NAME,
AND I DON'T KNOW YOURS.

403
00:38:13,740 --> 00:38:16,743
ALMA.  ALMA MOBLEY.

404
00:38:22,248 --> 00:38:26,252
- SHALL I TELL THE DEAN--
- OH, NO !  NOT--
NOT RIGHT AWAY.

405
00:38:26,252 --> 00:38:29,756
UM, HE'S--  I REALLY
STOPPED BY TO SEE YOU.

406
00:38:29,756 --> 00:38:32,258
I WONDERED IF YOU'RE NOT BUSY,
UH, TONIGHT,

407
00:38:32,258 --> 00:38:36,262
UH, IF YOU'RE NOT DOING
ANYTHING SPECIAL, MAYBE YOU'D
LIKE TO JOIN ME FOR DINNER.

408
00:38:36,262 --> 00:38:39,265
UH, I MEAN--
AH, WANDERLEY.

409
00:38:39,265 --> 00:38:42,268
YOU MUST HAVE BEEN
READING MY MIND.
[ Chuckles ]

410
00:38:45,271 --> 00:38:48,775
YOU'VE BEEN DOING
EXEMPLARY WORK, DONALD.
THANK YOU.

411
00:38:49,275 --> 00:38:51,778
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOUR PLANS ARE,
BUT I WAS JUST THINKING...

412
00:38:51,778 --> 00:38:54,781
MAYBE WE SHOULD
EXTEND YOUR STAY HERE
ANOTHER YEAR.

413
00:39:01,788 --> 00:39:04,791
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

414
00:39:04,791 --> 00:39:07,293
MAKE A WISH.

415
00:39:49,335 --> 00:39:51,838
[ Laughs ]

416
00:39:54,841 --> 00:39:57,844
[ Whooping ]

417
00:40:10,857 --> 00:40:14,360
IF YOU WANT TO MAKE LOVE
TO ME, YOU'D BETTER HURRY !

418
00:40:23,870 --> 00:40:25,872
[ Chuckles ]

419
00:40:27,373 --> 00:40:31,878
[ Thunder ]

420
00:40:47,894 --> 00:40:49,896
[ Exhales ]

421
00:40:51,397 --> 00:40:57,403
????

422
00:41:00,406 --> 00:41:03,910
DO YOU LIKE IT ?
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

423
00:41:08,915 --> 00:41:10,917
I'M FRIGHTENED
OF THUNDER.

424
00:41:20,426 --> 00:41:23,930
I GUESS I'D BETTER
STAY HERE TONIGHT.

425
00:41:25,932 --> 00:41:27,934
YES.

426
00:41:32,438 --> 00:41:36,943
???? [ Music Box Continues ]

427
00:41:36,943 --> 00:41:38,945
[ Laughs ]

428
00:41:38,945 --> 00:41:41,447
[ Chuckles ]

429
00:41:46,452 --> 00:41:49,455
AHHH !
I WANT YOU !

430
00:42:22,989 --> 00:42:24,991
I WANT ANOTHER KISS.

431
00:42:30,496 --> 00:42:32,498
WE'RE GOING TO BE LATE.

432
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:36,502
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT YOU, YOU KNOW ?

433
00:42:36,502 --> 00:42:39,005
THERE'S NOTHING MUCH
TO KNOW.  I'M JUST
AN OLD-FASHIONED GIRL.

434
00:42:39,005 --> 00:42:42,008
[ Laughs ]
I'LL SAY.

435
00:42:43,509 --> 00:42:47,513
- COME ON, TELL ME.
- NOT NOW.

436
00:42:49,015 --> 00:42:51,017
WELL, UH,
WHERE ARE YOU FROM ?

437
00:42:55,521 --> 00:42:58,524
YOU'RE ENGLISH, RIGHT ?
SO H-HOW'D YOU WIND UP
DOWN HERE ?

438
00:42:58,524 --> 00:43:03,029
NONE OF THAT MATTERS.
I WANT TO KNOW ABOUT YOU.

439
00:43:04,030 --> 00:43:06,032
TELL ME WHERE YOU LIVE.

440
00:43:06,032 --> 00:43:09,535
AH, JUST A COUPLE OF ROOMS.
NO, NO.
WHERE YOU GREW UP.

441
00:43:09,535 --> 00:43:13,539
AH, MILBURN ?

442
00:43:13,539 --> 00:43:15,541
WELL, IT'S JUST A GRAVE
OF A TOWN IN NEW ENGLAND.

443
00:43:16,042 --> 00:43:19,545
UH, NOTHIN'S CHANGED THERE
IN ABOUT 200 YEARS.

444
00:43:19,545 --> 00:43:24,550
SOUNDS LOVELY.
[ Snickers ]
IT'S NOT.  IT'S BORING.

445
00:43:31,057 --> 00:43:33,059
WILL YOU TAKE ME THERE
SOMETIME ?

446
00:43:33,059 --> 00:43:37,063
YEAH.
PROMISE ?

447
00:43:38,064 --> 00:43:40,066
YEAH,
I PROMISE.

448
00:43:45,571 --> 00:43:49,575
???? [ Classical Soprano Duet ]

449
00:43:59,085 --> 00:44:02,088
[ Dripping ]
[ Alma ]
NOW.

450
00:44:02,088 --> 00:44:06,592
???? [ Continues ]
I WANT YOU... NOW.

451
00:44:06,592 --> 00:44:08,594
[ Don ]
HERE ?

452
00:44:08,594 --> 00:44:14,100
HERE.
OR NEVER AGAIN.
???? [ Full Choir Joins ]

453
00:44:15,101 --> 00:44:17,103
[ Knob Jiggling ]

454
00:44:17,103 --> 00:44:22,608
[ Woman ]
THIS DOOR IS NOT TO BE LOCKED
AT ANY TIME.

455
00:44:22,608 --> 00:44:25,111
[ Whispering ]
THERE'S MRS. MEREDITH.

456
00:44:26,112 --> 00:44:29,615
OPEN THIS DOOR THIS INSTANT.
DO YOU HEAR ME ?

457
00:44:29,615 --> 00:44:33,619
[ Laughs ]

458
00:44:34,120 --> 00:44:36,122
DON'T STOP.

459
00:44:36,122 --> 00:44:40,626
DON'T STOP.  DON'T STOP.
DON'T STOP.

460
00:44:45,631 --> 00:44:47,633
[ Alma Moaning ]

461
00:44:47,633 --> 00:44:51,637
[ People Chattering ]

462
00:44:54,640 --> 00:44:57,643
???? [ Guitar ]

463
00:45:08,154 --> 00:45:10,156
[ Clears Throat ]

464
00:45:12,658 --> 00:45:15,161
YOU'RE NOT WEARING--
UM--

465
00:45:15,161 --> 00:45:18,664
WHERE'D YOU LEAVE 'EM ?

466
00:45:18,664 --> 00:45:22,168
[ Laughing ]
DID YOU LEAVE--

467
00:45:22,168 --> 00:45:26,172
[ Clears Throat ]
YOU FOLKS LIKE TO ORDER NOW ?

468
00:45:28,708 --> 00:45:32,712
- [ Laughing ]
- COME ON, TELL ME.  I'VE TOLD
YOU EVERYTHING ABOUT ME.

469
00:45:32,712 --> 00:45:35,214
NO SECRETS.
ALL RIGHT.

470
00:45:35,715 --> 00:45:37,717
NO.
THERE'S NO ONE ELSE
IN YOUR LIFE ?

471
00:45:37,717 --> 00:45:41,220
JUST YOU.
WELL.  BUT
THERE WAS SOMEONE.

472
00:45:41,721 --> 00:45:45,224
- LONG TIME AGO.
- YOU WERE IN LOVE
WITH HIM ?

473
00:45:45,224 --> 00:45:48,227
IT WASN'T ANYTHING
LIKE YOU'RE THINKING.

474
00:45:50,229 --> 00:45:52,231
JUST--
[ Laughs ]
JUST TELL ME THAT--

475
00:45:52,231 --> 00:45:54,734
TELL ME THAT
IT DOESN'T, UH--

476
00:45:54,734 --> 00:45:58,738
- HAVE ANYTHING TO DO WITH YOU ?
- IT WASN'T A GREAT LOVE.

477
00:46:00,239 --> 00:46:03,743
- NO.
- GOOD.

478
00:46:03,743 --> 00:46:06,746
BECAUSE I'M GOING TO BE,
AND I DON'T WANT THERE
TO BE ANYONE ELSE.

479
00:46:06,746 --> 00:46:09,749
JUST ME.
[ Laughs ]

480
00:46:12,752 --> 00:46:16,756
NOW LET ME TELL YOU
WHERE I'M GONNA TAKE YOU
NEXT WEEKEND.

481
00:46:16,756 --> 00:46:19,258
YOU HAVEN'T DONE ANY WORK
IN WEEKS.

482
00:46:19,258 --> 00:46:23,262
- I DON'T CARE.
- I'M A BAD INFLUENCE.

483
00:46:23,262 --> 00:46:26,265
YES, YOU ARE BAD.

484
00:46:36,776 --> 00:46:40,279
[ Screaming ]

485
00:46:52,792 --> 00:46:54,794
[ Clearing Throat ]

486
00:47:03,302 --> 00:47:05,805
WHAT IS IT, ALMA ?

487
00:47:10,810 --> 00:47:13,312
[ Dog Barking ]
WATER.

488
00:47:56,322 --> 00:47:59,825
LET'S, UH...
ELOPE.

489
00:48:06,332 --> 00:48:10,336
WE COULD, UH...
GO TO THE GREEK ISLANDS.

490
00:48:10,336 --> 00:48:13,339
CRETE.

491
00:48:14,340 --> 00:48:17,343
DON, I'D LOVE THAT.

492
00:48:17,343 --> 00:48:19,345
- BUT--
- BUT WHAT ?

493
00:48:19,845 --> 00:48:22,348
I'D RATHER GO TO MILBURN.

494
00:48:22,348 --> 00:48:24,350
[ Laughs ]

495
00:48:24,350 --> 00:48:26,352
NO.  NOT MILBURN.

496
00:48:26,352 --> 00:48:28,854
YOU'RE KIDDING, RIGHT ?

497
00:48:28,854 --> 00:48:32,358
DON'T YOU WANT
TO SHOW ME OFF
TO YOUR HOMETOWN ?

498
00:48:33,859 --> 00:48:36,862
[ Chuckles ]
I WANT TO MEET
YOUR FAMILY.

499
00:48:36,862 --> 00:48:40,866
WELL, MY MOTHER DIED
A LONG TIME AGO.
BUT YOUR FATHER,

500
00:48:41,367 --> 00:48:44,370
HE'S STILL ALIVE.
AH, MY FATHER AND I DON'T
GET ALONG ALL THAT WELL.

501
00:48:44,870 --> 00:48:47,873
SURELY THIS IS DIFFERENT.

502
00:48:47,873 --> 00:48:49,875
THIS IS OUR WEDDING.

503
00:48:53,379 --> 00:48:55,381
WHAT'S YOUR BROTHER LIKE ?

504
00:48:55,381 --> 00:48:58,384
[ Sighs ]

505
00:48:58,384 --> 00:49:00,386
HE'S MORE LIKE MY FATHER,
I GUESS.

506
00:49:00,386 --> 00:49:02,888
SUCCESSFUL.  AMBITIOUS.

507
00:49:03,889 --> 00:49:06,392
MORE OF A HUNTER.

508
00:49:09,395 --> 00:49:12,398
YOU DON'T REALLY
WANT TO GET MARRIED
IN MILBURN, DO YOU ?

509
00:49:13,899 --> 00:49:16,902
I WANT TO GET MARRIED
IN THE TOWN WHERE YOU
GREW UP.

510
00:49:17,903 --> 00:49:19,905
THE SAME CHURCH.

511
00:49:19,905 --> 00:49:22,908
I WANT TO WALK
DOWN THE AISLE...

512
00:49:22,908 --> 00:49:25,911
IN MY WHITE DRESS
AND VEIL,

513
00:49:25,911 --> 00:49:28,914
AND I WANT EVERYONE
TO BE THERE.

514
00:49:28,914 --> 00:49:31,917
YOUR FATHER,
HIS FRIENDS,

515
00:49:31,917 --> 00:49:33,919
THE WHOLE TOWN.

516
00:49:35,921 --> 00:49:37,923
ALL OF MILBURN.

517
00:50:27,473 --> 00:50:30,976
I WILL TAKE YOU PLACES...

518
00:50:30,976 --> 00:50:33,979
WHERE YOU HAVE NEVER BEEN.

519
00:50:35,481 --> 00:50:39,985
I WILL SHOW YOU THINGS
THAT YOU HAVE NEVER SEEN.

520
00:50:40,986 --> 00:50:43,489
ALMA ?

521
00:50:48,994 --> 00:50:52,498
AND I WILL SEE THE LIFE
RUN OUT OF YOU.

522
00:51:18,023 --> 00:51:19,525
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT ?

523
00:51:23,028 --> 00:51:25,531
ALMA ?

524
00:51:25,531 --> 00:51:29,034
[ Laughing ]

525
00:51:32,538 --> 00:51:35,541
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

526
00:52:03,769 --> 00:52:05,771
DO YOU REMEMBER ?

527
00:52:07,773 --> 00:52:09,775
THE FIRST NIGHT
YOU WERE HERE.

528
00:52:09,775 --> 00:52:11,777
IT WAS RAINING THEN.

529
00:52:23,289 --> 00:52:25,791
WHAT IS IT ?

530
00:52:26,292 --> 00:52:28,294
LET'S TALK TOMORROW.
NOW.

531
00:52:31,797 --> 00:52:33,799
I DON'T WANT TO GET
MARRIED FOR A WHILE.

532
00:52:36,302 --> 00:52:38,804
WHEN ?
I DON'T KNOW.

533
00:52:39,305 --> 00:52:41,807
MAYBE NOT AT ALL.

534
00:52:41,807 --> 00:52:45,811
YOU HAVE TO.
I'M SORRY.

535
00:52:45,811 --> 00:52:48,814
YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING !

536
00:52:53,819 --> 00:52:55,821
NO.

537
00:53:08,834 --> 00:53:11,337
???? [ Music Box ]

538
00:53:20,346 --> 00:53:23,349
[ Thunderclap ]

539
00:53:29,855 --> 00:53:31,857
[ Moaning ]
ALMA.

540
00:53:45,371 --> 00:53:47,373
ALMA !

541
00:53:48,374 --> 00:53:51,377
[ Panting ]

542
00:53:59,385 --> 00:54:02,388
ALMA, LISTEN--

543
00:54:04,390 --> 00:54:06,892
CAN I HELP YOU,
MR. WANDERLEY ?

544
00:54:06,892 --> 00:54:08,894
WHERE IS SHE ?

545
00:54:08,894 --> 00:54:12,398
MISS MOBLEY DID NOT TURN UP
FOR WORK THIS MORNING,
NOR DID SHE PHONE...

546
00:54:12,898 --> 00:54:14,900
TO SAY THAT
SHE WOULD BE ABSENT.

547
00:54:15,401 --> 00:54:17,903
THE DEAN IS MOST UPSET.

548
00:54:19,405 --> 00:54:23,909
YOU'RE LAX.  YOU'RE LAZY.
YOU'RE SLIPSHOD.

549
00:54:23,909 --> 00:54:29,381
YOU DISAPPEAR FOR DAYS
ON END WITHOUT SAYING
A WORD TO ANYONE.

550
00:54:29,381 --> 00:54:32,384
DISAPPOINTED ?

551
00:54:35,888 --> 00:54:39,858
I THOUGHT YOU
MADE A GOOD START.

552
00:55:15,177 --> 00:55:17,179
ALMA ?

553
00:55:33,696 --> 00:55:36,699
WAIT.  THAT'S
THE KIDS THERE ?
RIGHT.

554
00:55:36,699 --> 00:55:40,202
WHO IS IT ?
[ Woman ]
YOUR BROTHER ON 32.

555
00:55:40,703 --> 00:55:42,705
OKAY.

556
00:55:42,705 --> 00:55:45,708
HI, DONNIE.
AH, DAVID.

557
00:55:46,208 --> 00:55:48,711
I BEEN THINKIN' ABOUT YOU.
I'M GLAD YOU CALLED.

558
00:55:49,211 --> 00:55:50,713
UH, DAVE,
I GOTTA TALK TO YOU.

559
00:55:51,213 --> 00:55:54,717
YEAH.  I GOTTA TALK TO YOU.
I GOT SOME AMAZING NEWS.

560
00:55:54,717 --> 00:55:57,720
WHAT ?  ROBERT REDFORD
BOUGHT YOUR LIFE STORY ?

561
00:55:57,720 --> 00:55:59,722
[ Chuckles ]
NO, I'M SERIOUS.

562
00:56:00,222 --> 00:56:02,224
UM, I JUST DON'T KNOW
HOW TO TELL YOU.

563
00:56:02,224 --> 00:56:05,227
ALL RIGHT.  WELL,
TRY STARTING AT THE TOP.

564
00:56:05,227 --> 00:56:08,731
OKAY.  UM,
ABOUT A MONTH AGO,

565
00:56:08,731 --> 00:56:10,733
I WAS UP ON COLUMBUS AVENUE
ON BUSINESS,

566
00:56:11,233 --> 00:56:13,736
AND, UH, SOMEBODY
CALLED OUT YOUR NAME.

567
00:56:13,736 --> 00:56:15,738
UH-HUH.

568
00:56:15,738 --> 00:56:19,241
I TURNED AROUND,
AND THERE'S THIS
GREAT-LOOKING GIRL.

569
00:56:19,241 --> 00:56:23,746
SHE THINKS I'M YOU, RIGHT ?
WELL, I HOPE YOU
GOT AROUND TO TELLIN' HER.

570
00:56:23,746 --> 00:56:25,748
YES.  I GOT AROUND
TO TELLIN' HER.

571
00:56:28,751 --> 00:56:31,754
WHAT'S HER NAME, DAVE ?

572
00:56:32,254 --> 00:56:34,757
DONNIE.

573
00:56:34,757 --> 00:56:38,761
UH, SHE IS NOT THE PERSON
THAT YOU THINK SHE IS.

574
00:56:38,761 --> 00:56:41,764
[ Exhales ]
SHIT.

575
00:56:41,764 --> 00:56:45,768
SHE'S WORRIED YOU HAVE
THE WRONG IDEA ABOUT HER.

576
00:56:49,271 --> 00:56:51,273
EVERYTHING ABOUT HER
IS WRONG.

577
00:56:53,275 --> 00:56:56,278
GET AWAY FROM HER, DAVE.
SHE'S DANGEROUS.

578
00:56:56,278 --> 00:56:58,781
I CAN UNDERSTAND
YOU BEING UPSET.

579
00:56:59,281 --> 00:57:02,284
IF ALMA HAD WALKED OUT
ON ME TO MARRY YOU,
I'D SURE AS HELL RESENT YOU.

580
00:57:02,284 --> 00:57:04,787
[ Scoffs ]
I DON'T RESENT ANYTHING.

581
00:57:05,287 --> 00:57:06,789
OH, COME OFF IT.
IF YOU CAN'T ADMIT--

582
00:57:06,789 --> 00:57:10,292
SHUT THE HELL UP
AND LISTEN TO ME, DAVE.
[ Exhales ]

583
00:57:10,292 --> 00:57:16,298
LOOK AT HER.
ALL RIGHT ?
SHE IS NOT REAL.

584
00:57:16,298 --> 00:57:20,803
AND YOU KNOW, LIKE,
WHEN YOU TOUCH HER ?
SHE'S COLD.

585
00:57:20,803 --> 00:57:25,307
[ Sighs ]
I DON'T THINK WE'RE TALKIN'
ABOUT THE SAME WOMAN.

586
00:57:25,307 --> 00:57:27,309
[ Phone Disconnects ]

587
00:57:28,811 --> 00:57:31,814
[ Dial Tone ]

588
00:57:34,817 --> 00:57:38,821
WHEN THEY BROKE DOWN THE DOOR
TO DAVID'S APARTMENT,
NO ONE WAS THERE.

589
00:57:40,322 --> 00:57:42,324
SHE HAD SIMPLY VANISHED.

590
00:57:46,328 --> 00:57:48,831
THERE HAD NEVER BEEN
AN ALMA MOBLEY.

591
00:57:49,832 --> 00:57:51,834
[ Coughing ]

592
00:57:55,337 --> 00:57:56,839
[ Sighs ]

593
00:57:58,340 --> 00:58:02,845
I CAN VOUCH FOR THEIR MERIT.
HAVANA.

594
00:58:02,845 --> 00:58:05,848
WHAT ABOUT MY STORY ?

595
00:58:05,848 --> 00:58:08,350
WELL, THAT WAS QUITE A TALE,
YOUNG MAN.

596
00:58:08,851 --> 00:58:12,855
IT HAPPENED.
JUST THE WAY I TOLD YOU.

597
00:58:12,855 --> 00:58:15,357
[ Inhales ]

598
00:58:15,357 --> 00:58:18,360
WHY IS SHE HERE ?

599
00:58:18,360 --> 00:58:21,864
- [ Chuckles ]
SHE MUST HAVE HEARD YOU.
-[ Dogs Barking ]

600
00:58:21,864 --> 00:58:23,866
I KNOW YOU'RE SCARED.

601
00:58:23,866 --> 00:58:27,369
I'M SCARED TOO.

602
00:58:27,870 --> 00:58:31,874
I'M LUCKY TO HAVE ESCAPED
WHATEVER SENT DAVID
OUT THAT WINDOW.

603
00:58:32,374 --> 00:58:35,878
BUT I THINK...
IF WE HELP EACH OTHER--

604
00:58:36,378 --> 00:58:40,883
SOUNDS LIKE KNUTE ROCKNE
BEFORE A BIG GAME,
DOESN'T HE, RICKY ?

605
00:58:43,886 --> 00:58:46,388
[ Don ]
THAT'S ALMA MOBLEY.

606
00:58:51,393 --> 00:58:54,897
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

607
00:58:57,399 --> 00:59:00,903
[ Doc ]
I KNEW THIS
WAS GOING TO HAPPEN.

608
00:59:00,903 --> 00:59:04,406
- COINCIDENCE.
- I DON'T THINK SO.

609
00:59:04,406 --> 00:59:06,909
NEITHER DO I.

610
00:59:06,909 --> 00:59:09,912
[ Doc Coughing ]

611
00:59:11,914 --> 00:59:14,416
NO.

612
00:59:17,419 --> 00:59:21,423
I'M AN OLD MAN
AND OFTEN I'M RUDE.

613
00:59:21,423 --> 00:59:27,429
WE'LL ALL BE VERY GRATEFUL
FOR ANY HELP YOU CAN GIVE US.

614
00:59:27,930 --> 00:59:30,432
I KNEW IT.
I JUST KNEW IT !

615
00:59:35,437 --> 00:59:39,942
THE LAST TIME I SAW ALMA,
SHE WAS WEARING THIS.

616
00:59:39,942 --> 00:59:42,945
WHERE'D YOU GET IT ?

617
00:59:42,945 --> 00:59:44,947
A LITTLE PRESENT
FROM GREGORY BATE.

618
00:59:44,947 --> 00:59:49,451
- THISHADTO HAPPEN.
IT JUST HAD TO !
- THAT'S ENOUGH !

619
00:59:49,451 --> 00:59:52,955
OH, NO.  NO.
WE-- WE MUST TALK ABOUT IT.

620
00:59:52,955 --> 00:59:55,457
PLEASE, LET ME TELL YOU
ABOUT MY NIGHTMARES.
NO !

621
00:59:55,457 --> 00:59:57,960
- MILLY !
- OH, NO !  PLEASE.
LET'S NOT STOP !

622
00:59:57,960 --> 01:00:02,464
OH, MY FRIENDS !
MY DEAR, DEAR FRIENDS.
[ Ricky ]  EASY, JOHN.

623
01:00:02,464 --> 01:00:06,468
- PLEASE LET ME TALK
ABOUT IT !  PLEASE !
- GET OUT.  ALL OF YOU.

624
01:00:06,468 --> 01:00:09,972
ALL THIS TALK OF GRAVES
AND GHOULS.  OUT !
[ John ]  PLEASE LISTEN TO ME !

625
01:00:09,972 --> 01:00:14,977
LISTEN TO ME !  PLEASE !
PLEASE !  LISTEN !

626
01:00:21,283 --> 01:00:24,286
[ Breathing Unevenly ]

627
01:00:54,316 --> 01:00:56,318
[ Moans ]

628
01:00:56,818 --> 01:01:00,822
[ Contralto ]
?? MY FACE ??

629
01:01:00,822 --> 01:01:05,327
?? BIDST NOT FORGET ??

630
01:01:05,327 --> 01:01:12,334
?? WHERE E'ER THOU ART ??

631
01:01:12,334 --> 01:01:18,340
?? FORGET MY FACE ????

632
01:01:18,340 --> 01:01:20,842
NO, I'M NOT GOING IN THERE.

633
01:01:20,842 --> 01:01:23,345
NO, I'M NOT !
I'M NOT GOING IN THERE !

634
01:01:23,345 --> 01:01:26,348
NO !  OH, YEAH, MAYBE.
NO, I'M NOT GOING IN !

635
01:01:26,848 --> 01:01:29,351
NO !  NOO-OO !

636
01:01:35,857 --> 01:01:40,362
IT'S JUST AS I TOLD YOU.
NO PULSE AT ALL.

637
01:01:42,364 --> 01:01:45,867
NO PULSE AT ALL.
SHE'S DEAD.

638
01:01:47,369 --> 01:01:49,371
LIKE I SAID.

639
01:01:49,371 --> 01:01:51,873
- [ Screaming ]
- JOHN !

640
01:01:52,374 --> 01:01:56,378
- NO !  NO !
- [ Milly ]
NO !

641
01:01:58,380 --> 01:02:01,383
- JOHN !
- CAN'T MOVE.

642
01:02:01,883 --> 01:02:04,886
YOU'RE DEAD !
IT'S ME.

643
01:02:04,886 --> 01:02:09,391
- I DON'T BELIEVE IT !
NO PULSE.
- MILLY.  MILLY.

644
01:02:09,391 --> 01:02:13,895
NO.  NO !  NO.

645
01:02:14,396 --> 01:02:17,399
[ Moans ]

646
01:02:17,899 --> 01:02:21,403
[ Dogs Barking ]

647
01:02:30,912 --> 01:02:33,915
I'LL BE DOWN
IN JUST A MINUTE, MISS.

648
01:02:37,919 --> 01:02:40,238
[ Wind Howling ]

649
01:02:54,352 --> 01:02:57,856
MILLY ?
RISE AND SHINE NOW.

650
01:03:00,859 --> 01:03:04,362
THERE.
[ Groans ]

651
01:03:04,863 --> 01:03:07,866
IS IT LATE ?
11:30.

652
01:03:07,866 --> 01:03:11,870
OH.
YOU NEEDED THE REST.

653
01:03:12,370 --> 01:03:13,872
COME ON, NOW.
[ Sighs ]

654
01:03:14,372 --> 01:03:16,374
I BROUGHT YOU
A NICE CUP OF TEA,

655
01:03:16,374 --> 01:03:19,878
THOUGH YOU HARDLY DESERVE IT
AFTER LAST NIGHT.

656
01:03:19,878 --> 01:03:23,882
WHAT DO YOU MEAN ?
YOU KNOW VERY WELL.

657
01:03:26,885 --> 01:03:30,388
- YOU ATTACKED ME !
- I WHAT ?

658
01:03:30,388 --> 01:03:33,892
YOU STARED AT ME AS IF
YOU'D NEVER SEEN ME BEFORE.

659
01:03:41,399 --> 01:03:43,401
OH, MILLY.

660
01:03:45,403 --> 01:03:47,906
FORGIVE ME.

661
01:03:47,906 --> 01:03:50,909
TOO MANY OF THOSE
DARN STORIES.

662
01:03:50,909 --> 01:03:55,413
TOO MUCH OF THAT HIGH AND MIGHTY
MR. SEARS JAMES.

663
01:03:58,416 --> 01:04:01,336
OH, DEAR GOD,
I'M TIRED.

664
01:04:01,336 --> 01:04:06,341
TELL ME.
YOU CAN TRUST ME.

665
01:04:08,844 --> 01:04:10,846
BAD DREAMS AGAIN.
YES.

666
01:04:11,346 --> 01:04:14,349
IT'S ALL OVER.
DAYLIGHT NOW.

667
01:04:14,349 --> 01:04:16,351
JOHN ?

668
01:04:19,354 --> 01:04:21,356
I CAN'T REMEMBER.

669
01:04:22,858 --> 01:04:24,860
"SHE MOVED."

670
01:04:26,862 --> 01:04:29,364
YES, SHE MOVED.
WHO MOVED ?

671
01:04:31,366 --> 01:04:35,370
SHE COULDN'T--
COULDN'T HAVE.
SHE--

672
01:04:35,370 --> 01:04:38,373
THERE'S NO PULSE.
SHE'S DEAD.

673
01:04:40,375 --> 01:04:43,378
FOR GOD'S SAKE, JOHN.
WHO ?

674
01:04:43,378 --> 01:04:45,380
SHE WAS--

675
01:04:50,886 --> 01:04:53,388
NO.  IT'S J-J-JUST
THE JIMJAMS.

676
01:04:53,889 --> 01:04:55,390
NO.  TELL ME.

677
01:04:57,392 --> 01:05:00,395
NOW, GO ON, GO ON.
STOP FUSSING.

